snippet.textDisplay:
A game done right; an ageless gem in a jewelry box of countless failed wanna-be's. It may don a coat of dust now, but still it stands on its own two feet. No lootboxes, no DLC, no hand-holding, no childish references, no fear of the media, nothing.

Just you, pickups and powerups, that guy on the other side, and a higher skill ceiling than Face's twin towers.

Just you, pickups and powerups, that guy on the other side, and a higher skill ceiling than Face's twin towers.
